{"article_id":"npNRp6FVPVWqgP6k","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Research Suggests","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Gun Background Checks Work ,","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"But They 're Not Everything","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"Here 's one topic","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Americans can bank on hearing about in next week 's State of the Union address :","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"gun control .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"The reaction to President Obama 's announced gun-control measures this week was swift and entirely as expected .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"Gun-control advocates and many Democrats applauded his efforts ;","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"gun-rights groups and many Republicans loudly denounced the orders as executive overreach .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"Expanded background checks are central to the president 's proposals .","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"His order does n't rewrite existing laws ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"but it would broaden the scope of who is in the gun-selling business .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"It would require more gun sellers online and at gun shows to be licensed","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"( and perform checks )","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"among other things .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"`` Let me be clear :","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"It 's not where you are located","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"but what you are doing","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"that determines","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"whether you are engaged in the business","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"of dealing in firearms , ''","depth":14},{"id":21,"text":"Attorney General Loretta Lynch told reporters this week .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"So would those extra checks bring down America 's high levels of gun deaths ?","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"Gun policy experts","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"who spoke to NPR","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"say","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"it could ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"but","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"if so ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"that it would only make a dent .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Two recent studies provide evidence","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"that background checks can significantly curb gun violence .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"In one , researchers found","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"that a 1995 Connecticut law","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"requiring gun buyers to get permits","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"( which themselves required background checks )","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"was associated with a 40 percent decline in gun homicides and a 15 percent drop in suicides .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Similarly ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"when researchers studied Missouri 's 2007 repeal of its permit-to-purchase law ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"they found an associated increase in gun homicides by 23 percent , as well as a 16-percent increase in suicides .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"Those are some huge results","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"- one expert called the Missouri study `` the strongest evidence","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"that background checks really matter , ''","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"as The New Republic reported -","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"but as with lots of social-science research , there 's some fuzziness","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"as to what the results mean .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"One caveat is that these studies are n't about background checks alone .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"Instead , they 're about permit-to-purchase laws ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"under which people had to go to local law enforcement","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"to get a permit and , therefore , a background check .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"That difference might have impacted the results ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"explained Daniel Webster , a co-author on both studies .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"that being forced to get a permit from law enforcement might do more","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"to deter a straw purchaser , for example ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"than getting a check at a nearby store .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Furthermore , he added","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"because so many factors influence gun violence in different ways ,","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"it 's hard to say","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"how much the effects","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"seen in Connecticut and Missouri","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"would also happen in other states .","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"In addition , a stand your ground law","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"enacted in Missouri in 2007","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"may have affected the results .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Still , other academic research points to the laws ' effectiveness as well .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"In a 2015 analysis of studies","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"published over the course of 15 years ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"Webster and co-author Garen Wintemute found","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"that expanding background checks could `` have protective effects against lethal violence , ''","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"and that permit-to-purchase laws in particular help curb murders and suicides .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"They also found","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"that background checks help keep guns out of the hands of criminals ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"but that it 's less certain whether that in turn leads to less violence .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"There 's no perfect consensus","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"on how well background-check laws work .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"A 2000 study found","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"that the 1994 Brady Act","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"- which instituted not only background checks but waiting periods at first -","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"did not reduce either homicide or suicide rates .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"A CDC task force also found in a 2003 review `` inconsistent findings ''","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"as to whether restricting gun access through background checks works","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"and insufficient evidence","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"as to whether an array of other gun laws are effective .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"However , the CDC also said","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"that its findings did n't mean","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"that gun laws do n't work ;","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"rather , it said","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"it needed to study the topic more .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"Gun-policy researchers say","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"they want to better study background checks","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"( as well as many other policies ) ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"but a couple of hurdles stand in the way .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Part of the problem is that good studies on the effectiveness of background checks are pretty rare ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"according to Webster .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"One reason is that it 's hard to find good test cases","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"to study .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"`` There 's not a lot of change or variation","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"[ in laws ]","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"to study in recent times , ''","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"`` The vast majority of these laws have been on the books for many , many decades . ''","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"`` One of the big problems is that the feds have not funded good research in this area , ''","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"said David Hemenway , director of the Harvard Injury Control Research Center and an expert on firearm-related injuries .","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"He points to federal restrictions ,","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"passed in 1996 ,","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"that said","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"the Centers for Disease Control could not use its funding","depth":15},{"id":109,"text":"to `` advocate or promote gun control . ''","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"That caused the CDC to back away from gun research almost entirely .","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"Outside organizations could pick up that slack ,","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"Hemenway added ,","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"but they have not done so .","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"`` The foundations have n't done a good job ,","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"because it 's such a controversial area , ''","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"he said .","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"You do n't want to get involved .","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"So we know some things ,","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"but we do n't know","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"as well","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"as you would hope ,","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"given the enormity of the problem . ''","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"While some scholarly evidence suggests","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"that background checks reduce crime ,","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"seeing evidence in recent mass shootings is tougher .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"As the New York Times found in a December investigation ,","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"the guns","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"used in many recent high-profile shootings","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"were purchased legally by people","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"who passed background checks .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"Importantly , though , to the extent","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"that background-check laws on the books might have prevented mass shootings ,","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"it 's impossible to compile similar lists of incidents","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"that would have occurred ,","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"were it not for those laws .","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"One other thing","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"recent shootings say","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"is that the current background-check system has some gaping holes in it .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"For example , FBI Director James Comey said in July 2015","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"that Dylann Roof ,","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"who is accused of killing nine at a South Carolina church last year ,","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"should not have passed a background check .","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"Because information about his admission to a narcotics charge never reached an FBI examiner","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"handling his check ,","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"as the Washington Post reported ,","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"Roof was able to buy his gun .","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"In addition , some states are doing a poor job","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"of submitting mental health records to NICS ,","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"as Politico 's Kevin Cirilli writes ,","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"allowing some sick people to obtain guns .","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"Cirilli points to Virginia Tech shooter Seung-Hui Cho ,","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"who had a history of mental illness","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"before he killed 32 people in 2007 .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"As it stands ,","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"around 1.6 percent of 148 million background checks","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"( that is , more than 2 million )","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"between 1994 and 2012 were denied ,","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"according to federal statistics .","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"One of the most important questions to this discussion is impossible to answer precisely :","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"how many guns are obtained","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"without background checks ?","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"While there are n't exact numbers on this ,","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"the figure could still be substantial .","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"Using 2004 data ,","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"around 18 percent of gun transactions involved private sellers , buyers ' family members or friends or `` other '' sources ,","depth":14},{"id":166,"text":"as the Washington Post 's Glenn Kessler found last year .","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"A majority of those sources were not licensed dealers","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"( and therefore were not required to conduct background checks ) .","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"According to the figures","depth":15},{"id":170,"text":"cited by Kessler ,","depth":15},{"id":171,"text":"7 percent of guns were obtained from gun shows","depth":15},{"id":172,"text":"( and many of those sales probably underwent background checks ) .","depth":15},{"id":173,"text":"But data suggests","depth":14},{"id":174,"text":"that gun shows do n't directly supply many of the guns","depth":15},{"id":175,"text":"used in crimes .","depth":15},{"id":176,"text":"Spokespeople from the National Rifle Association and National Shooting Sports Foundation , a trade group for gun sellers , both also pointed NPR to government data","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"showing","depth":15},{"id":178,"text":"that less than 1 percent of prison inmates in 1997 said","depth":16},{"id":179,"text":"they got their guns from gun shows .","depth":16},{"id":180,"text":"Meanwhile , nearly 80 percent obtained their guns from friends , family or `` street ''","depth":15},{"id":181,"text":"( illegal )","depth":15},{"id":182,"text":"sources .","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"All of this very well may mean","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"that ,","depth":11},{"id":185,"text":"as gun-rights advocates like Florida Republican Sen. Marco Rubio often point out ,","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"criminals will simply obtain guns through some avenue other than stores .","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"That would mean","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"that background checks do n't deter those people ,","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"and , therefore , that expanding them to more online or private or gun show sales would do little .","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"But there are other possible conclusions .","depth":8},{"id":191,"text":"A recent study of offenders in the Chicago area found","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"most obtained their guns from `` personal connections , not from gun stores or by theft . ''","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"While that study suggested to some","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"that background checks are ineffective ,","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"one of the authors , Duke University 's Philip Cook , disagrees .","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"`` This research demonstrates","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"that current federal and local regulations are having a big effect on the availability of guns to criminals in Chicago , ''","depth":15},{"id":198,"text":"he said in a release .","depth":14},{"id":199,"text":"`` They ca n't buy their guns from stores , the way","depth":15},{"id":200,"text":"most people do ,","depth":15},{"id":201,"text":"and are instead largely constrained to making private deals with acquaintances ,","depth":15},{"id":202,"text":"who may or may not be willing and able to provide what they want . ''","depth":15},{"id":203,"text":"Lawrence Keane , general counsel for the National Shooting Sports Foundation , told NPR","depth":13},{"id":204,"text":"that `` the industry has always been supportive of the background check system , ''","depth":13},{"id":205,"text":"though he also said","depth":13},{"id":206,"text":"he has doubts about how much good the new proposals will do .","depth":13},{"id":207,"text":"In addition , his group is strongly opposed to making background checks universal .","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"Researchers Hemenway and Webster both think","depth":12},{"id":209,"text":"the president 's executive actions could have a modest effect on gun violence .","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"For his part , Hemenway thinks","depth":14},{"id":211,"text":"universal background checks would be an effective first step ,","depth":14},{"id":212,"text":"but what he thinks would be more fruitful in the long term has more to do with innovation than legislative action .","depth":13},{"id":213,"text":"`` In the long run , we should be spending a lot of money on figuring out technological fixes , ''","depth":14},{"id":214,"text":"he said .","depth":14},{"id":215,"text":"`` The easiest one is to make guns better for home protection and much , much less dangerous and less likely to be stolen . ''","depth":13}],"relations":[{"parent":431,"left":218,"right":430,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":218,"left":0,"right":217,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":217,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":430,"left":244,"right":429,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":244,"left":220,"right":243,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":220,"left":219,"right":5,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":219,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":243,"left":222,"right":242,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":6,"right":221,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":242,"left":9,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":234,"right":240,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":233,"right":22,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":233,"left":226,"right":232,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":223,"right":225,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":225,"left":224,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":224,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":15,"right":231,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":231,"left":230,"right":21,"relation":"attribution","nuclea